[The following comments are intended to amplify a few points
mentioned in the article above:]
From: "William Sprigg" <wsprigg@nas.edu>
We need to emphasize that "a proposal to develop an international
research and information dissemination strategy on this subject has been
submitted to the EPA for coordination and funding among several U.S.
agencies." Also, we might highlight one of the benefits will be
long-lead alerts of potential health problems. Such would allow more
rapid, mobilized, targeted-for-effect, actions (eg. mosquito control and
increased surveillance). Another point to clarify in future might be
that the proposal is from the National Research Council representing both
the National Academy of Sciences and the Institute of Medicine.
